>> Begin forwarded message:
>>=20
>> From: "Sussman, Gabriel F 2LT USARMY NG TNARNG (USA)" =
<gabriel.f.sussman.mil@army.mil>
>> Subject: Re: TNMAN 26 Bridge Assessment Notes - [UNCLASSIFIED]
>> Date: February 18, 2026 at 13:32:36 EST
>> To: tnsg.2nd co <tnsg.2nd.co@tnstateguard.org>
>> Cc: Chris Beaver <chris.beaver@tnstateguard.org>, "Callison, T R =
(Trint) MAJ USARMY NG TNARNG (USA)" <trinity.r.callison.mil@army.mil>, =
"Crandall, Kristin K MAJ USARMY NG TNARNG (USA)" =
<kristin.k.crandall.mil@army.mil>
>>=20
>> UNCLASSIFIED
>>=20
>> R/LTC Estes,
>>=20
>> Good afternoon, Sir. Thank you for the update. As you probably know, =
I am currently at SBOLC, so I may be less involved than before, but I am =
still here to support the new Primary Planners, MAJ Callison and MAJ =
Crandall. There are a few questions that I have relating to what you =
shared. Based on previous discussions for Bridge Assessments, I believe =
that we were only going to have a handful of people that can be =
transported to the Bridge site by UH-60 Blackhawk. Is this still the =
case? I remember the number of authorized personnel being 6, but I can =
confirm with the TNNG SAO.
>>=20
>> Additionally, I have the TDOT contacts that you all had spoken with =
during our previous planning meeting below:
>>=20
>> Errol Christos (errol.christos@tn.gov) - TDOT TEMA LNO
>> Lee Bogle (Lee.Bogle@tn.gov) - TDOT
>>=20
>>=20
>> I appreciate your team working with FAA to receive proper UAS waivers =
before conducting mission. We also need to work with TDOT to ensure that =
we have permission to land a UH-60 and utilize the areas around the =
bridge locations. If we do not have permission, we will have to adjust =
the plan quickly before it becomes too late.
>>=20
>> I am not sure if you were able to see the emails I sent in January, =
but below are some RFI's that we need to determine to conduct the TNSG =
field exercises.
>>=20
>> Holston AAP Security (3rd Regiment)
>> -How many personnel will be on-site total?
>> -For the Security Patrols, will they be mounted or dismounted?
>> -If mounted, what vehicles and how many will be utilized =
(civilian/GSAs)
>> -If dismounted, does your personnel intend to be armed (real world)
>> -If they intend on being armed, do they all have qualifications that =
allow them to be armed in a civilian capacity? (I am unsure of if there =
is a separate law that allows TNSG to carry under SAD, when unauthorized =
in a civilian capacity).
>> -What shifts do you intend on running security? (24hr?)
>> -Are there any specific areas around Holston that you are =
specifically wanting/not wanting to pull security around?
>> -How many drones are you intending on utilizing?
>> -What are the size of the drones? (estimate of L/W)
>>=20
>> JBAT at I-40 (2nd Regiment)
>> -Do we have approval from the State to utilize the proposed area for =
Bridge assessments?
>> -If not, does the request need to come from TDOT or from the TN =
Military Department?
>> -Is there a plan from TDOT to restrict or shut down the bridges while =
you are assessing it or while the UH-60 lands?
>> -Are you able to make a Real World risk assessment for conducting the =
JBAT, especially if it will be an active roadway, on a river, in =
Spring/Summer? I just want to make sure that we take in consideration =
the risk that we are taking, even if the drones will do most of the =
close-up assessing. If you believe the Security element for SG requires =
a Risk Assessment, I would appreciate that as well, Sir.
>>=20
>> Thank you for your time,
>>=20
>> Gabriel F Sussman
>> 2LT, SC
>> Training Officer, J3/7 DOMS
>> 1/278th ACR S-6
>> Tennessee National Guard
>> Personal: 615-663-2360
>>=20
>>=20
>> UNCLASSIFIED
>>=20
>> From: Chris Beaver <chris@beaverengineering.com>
>> Subject: RE: TNMAN 26 Bridge Question - [UNCLASSIFIED]
>> Date: December 4, 2025 at 15:09:41 EST
>> To: "Beaver, Chris" <chris.beaver@tnstateguard.org>, "Sussman, =
Gabriel F 2LT USARMY NG TNARNG (USA)" <gabriel.f.sussman.mil@army.mil>
>> Cc: "robert.garner@tnstateguard.org" =
<robert.garner@tnstateguard.org>, "steven.estes@tnstateguard.org" =
<steven.estes@tnstateguard.org>, "kevin.stewart@tnstateguard.org" =
<kevin.stewart@tnstateguard.org>
>>=20
>> We can accommodate all that you are talking about.
>> =20
>> My goals (wish list) are:
>> 1.       Transfer Drone data to multiple agencies and the use of =
Drones in a joint effort.
>>                 The drone mission could be Bridge Assessment, Area =
Security, Search and Rescue, LIDAR Survey
>>                 The Joint effort would be to coordinate directly with =
NG
>>                 Success would be: The agency successfully receives =
the data, that its accurate, and that its timely
>> 2.       Conduct damage assessment of a critical Bridge and report =
our findings to multiple agencies
>>                 NG, TDOT, TEMA all have different reporting formats,
>>                 Establish rapport with NG, TDOT, and TEMA
>>                 Success would be: Accurate, timely, and correct =
format for each of the agencies.
>> 3.       Conduct SECFOR for the Engineers
>>                 Success would be: That our Security Forces can =
coordinate directly with SG, NG, TDOT, and TEMA.
>>                 And provide adequate security as the mission =
dictates.
>> =20
>> COA 1:
>>               =20
>> Leave the drones at home and conduct the assessment with a small team =
of Engineers and Security.  The Drones could be flown locally, as the =
primary goal is the successful transfer of data to multiple agencies, =
primarily NG.  To accomplish that goal it does not really matter where =
the drones are flown or what they are looking at.=20
>> =20
>>             Advantages:
>>             This accomplishes at least 2 out 3 of our goals
>>             Our guys would absolutely love to fly up there
>>             Significantly reduces our support needs
>> =20
>>             COA 2:
>> =20
>> We go for all 3 goals, stated above.  The drone we would use weighs =
10-20 lbs (case and unit).  The case is 46" x 15" x 16" (see attached =
photo).  We would also bring a smaller back up drone that fits in a =
backpack.
>> =20
>>             Advantages
>>             Same as above but accomplishes all 3 goals
>> =20
>> Per our discussion:
>> The number of PAX at a minimum would 3-Engineers, 1-Coms/Technician =
(Simpson), 2-Security =3D 6 absolute minimum, (if we can add more we =
would like to).
>> =20
>> =20
>> Possible Injects:
>> 1.     Fly drone to observe possible Enemy OP positions (using =
thermal)
>> 2.     Fly drone to observe for enemy activity on the Holston River =
along the base
>> 3.     Fly drone to conduct LIDAR survey of an Area of Interest.
>> 4.     Deploy SECFOR to an OP or Area of Interest and report =
observations
>> =20
>> =20
>> StarLink: We will need a StarLink from TEMA most likely.  The data is =
too big for Cellular Hot Spot.
>> =20
>> =20
>> =20
>> Chris Beaver
>> P.E.; LTC (ret)
>> President and Owner
>> =20
>> Beaver Engineering, Inc
>> 7378 Cockrill Bend Blvd
>> Nashville, TN 37209
>> =20
>> (m) 615-415-1866
>> (o) 615-350-8124
>>=20


